Assmang to Increase Ferromanganese Output With Conversion of Two Furnaces

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-06-30T14:04:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/assmang-to-increase-ferromanganese-output-with-conversion-of-two-furnaces.html
Assmang Ltd., which is jointly
controlled by  Assore Ltd. (ASR)  and  African Rainbow Minerals Ltd. (ARI) ,
said it’s decided to convert its No. 2 and No. 3 furnaces at
Machadodorp to produce high carbon ferromanganese.  The conversion will increase Assmang’s production by about
100,000 metric tons a year, bringing its total capacity to
375,000 tons, the company said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  